  "description": "Today, my goals include handling what\u0026rsquo;s in my \u0026ldquo;content triage,\u0026rdquo; which is, at the moment, older babbles, including some that got syndicated onto my Fediverse profile. Then, I\u0026rsquo;ll pull my Letters to the Web into the triage, and hopefully get to them today or tomorrow.\nSo far, I\u0026rsquo;m finding Obsidian comfortable enough to use, and am enjoying knowing that I\u0026rsquo;m on the same note-taking app that some of my friends use. (Though I probably use it the most, given the volume I can babble and write, and my aspirations with regards to like, digital gardening, vernacular autoethnosis, and agential semioverses, among other made-up things.\n",
